1
00:00:01,702 --> 00:00:03,370
Narrator: Previously on
"jojo’s bizarre adventure"...

2
00:00:03,403 --> 00:00:05,805
♪

3
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:07,407
Polnareff: What the hell?!

4
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,343
Hol horse: Hell, yeah!

5
00:00:09,376 --> 00:00:11,345
( Polnareff gasping )

6
00:00:11,378 --> 00:00:13,447
Mondatta: "’now, hol horse,’
mondatta instructed,

7
00:00:13,480 --> 00:00:16,450
"’stick your fingers all the way
up polnareff’s nose,

8
00:00:16,483 --> 00:00:17,918
"’and then we’ll win!

9
00:00:17,951 --> 00:00:20,587
"’they’re out cold
from losing all that blood.

10
00:00:20,621 --> 00:00:22,256
"’lucky you, hol horse!

11
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:24,758
this is your chance
to finish them off for good!’"

12
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:26,860
hol horse: So when is
this so-called chance

13
00:00:26,894 --> 00:00:29,764
supposed to get here,
and what do I do ’til then?

14
00:00:29,796 --> 00:00:32,332
Polnareff: Excuse me, hol horse.

15
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:34,535
Uh, what the hell
are you doing?

16
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:35,969
hol horse:
You’re not the only one

17
00:00:36,003 --> 00:00:37,605
who wants the answer
to that question.

18
00:00:37,638 --> 00:00:38,906
avdol:
What’s the matter, polnareff?

19
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:40,474
Horse: Shit! What now?!

20
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:42,442
They’re on me
like white on rice!

21
00:00:42,476 --> 00:00:43,877
Damn it! How the hell

22
00:00:43,911 --> 00:00:47,348
do I make the rest of this
stupid prediction come true?

23
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:50,718
Joseph: Hey, polnareff, did you
find the person tailing us?

24
00:00:50,751 --> 00:00:52,453
Avdol: Say something.

25
00:00:52,486 --> 00:00:55,356
Polnareff: Avdol and the others,
they’ll be here soon.

26
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:57,391
( Mondatta gasps )

27
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:04,398
Hol horse: Damn it. How am I
gonna get out of this one?

28
00:01:04,431 --> 00:01:05,866
Polnareff: Chario--

29
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:08,402
hol horse: Hold it right there.

30
00:01:08,435 --> 00:01:10,771
( Polnareff sputters )
this is bad.

31
00:01:10,804 --> 00:01:13,707
hol horse: I-i’m the--
the fastest quick draw around.

32
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,809
Now don’t move, or you’re dead.

33
00:01:15,843 --> 00:01:18,412
joseph: Hey,
did you say something?

34
00:01:18,445 --> 00:01:19,413
Polnareff?

35
00:01:19,446 --> 00:01:20,614
( Hol horse groans )

36
00:01:24,551 --> 00:01:26,386
Avdol: Polnareff!

37
00:01:28,822 --> 00:01:30,891
( Hol horse gasping )

38
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:37,564
- avdol: Huh?
- Jotaro and Joseph: Hmm?

39
00:01:37,598 --> 00:01:38,766
( Polnareff chuckles )

40
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:42,502
Avdol: Hang on.

41
00:01:42,536 --> 00:01:44,471
You’ve been here
the entire time?

42
00:01:44,505 --> 00:01:47,742
What’s wrong? Did you find
someone following us or not?

43
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:50,877
Polnareff: Well, uh...

44
00:01:50,911 --> 00:01:53,347
Hol horse: This is getting
uglier by the second.

45
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:54,781
They’ve backed me into a corner.

46
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:56,450
according to
that fool comic book,

47
00:01:56,483 --> 00:01:58,051
I was supposed
to get my big chance

48
00:01:58,085 --> 00:02:01,488
after I stuck my fingers
up polnareff’s nose,

49
00:02:01,522 --> 00:02:03,657
but everything has gone south,

50
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:06,993
and i’m about to be
in a whole world of trouble!

51
00:02:07,027 --> 00:02:09,029
♪

52
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:13,066
( Singing in Japanese )

53
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:35,622
Avdol: Is everything
all right, polnareff?

54
00:02:35,656 --> 00:02:36,991
Polnareff: Uh, of course.

55
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:40,027
hol horse: Well,
now i’ve really stepped in it.

56
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:43,397
If avdol finds me,
i’m as good as dead.

57
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,965
I think i’m gonna cry.

58
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:47,801
Had I known something
like this was gonna happen,

59
00:02:47,835 --> 00:02:50,004
I would have just blown him away
from a distance.

60
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:54,008
( Growls ) Mondatta, this is
all your fault. You know that?

61
00:02:54,041 --> 00:02:55,676
That fool polnareff’s sword

62
00:02:55,709 --> 00:02:59,012
would have had nothing
on my gun. Damn it!

63
00:02:59,046 --> 00:03:00,814
- Avdol: Polnareff?
- Hol horse: Hmm?

64
00:03:00,848 --> 00:03:02,717
( Scraping )

65
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:04,551
You waiting for an invitation?

66
00:03:04,585 --> 00:03:05,820
Tell ’em to scram,

67
00:03:05,853 --> 00:03:07,688
because I swear to you,
polnareff,

68
00:03:07,721 --> 00:03:10,958
if i’m found out,
i’m taking you down with me.

69
00:03:10,991 --> 00:03:13,727
( Polnareff stammers )
i-i was wrong.

70
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,995
No one was tailing us.

71
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:16,630
guess it was
just my imagination.

72
00:03:16,663 --> 00:03:17,631
( Hol horse sighs )

73
00:03:17,664 --> 00:03:19,432
All: Hmm...

74
00:03:19,466 --> 00:03:22,369
Avdol: I see, and is there
any particular reason

75
00:03:22,402 --> 00:03:24,938
you’re nonchalantly standing
in the corner like that?

76
00:03:24,972 --> 00:03:27,141
( Polnareff gasping )

77
00:03:27,174 --> 00:03:28,942
( Emperor clicks )

78
00:03:28,976 --> 00:03:30,478
hol horse:
Tell ’em that you wanted

79
00:03:30,511 --> 00:03:32,013
to find a place to take a leak.

80
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,648
do it, or i’ll
put a bullet in your head.

81
00:03:34,681 --> 00:03:36,750
Polnareff: Oh,
I had to take a whiz

82
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:39,586
and couldn’t find a toilet,
so what can you do?

83
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:41,021
- ( Laughs )
- Avdol: Are you serious?

84
00:03:41,054 --> 00:03:43,557
joseph: Come on.
You were peeing in the street?

85
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:47,027
Even after all this time,
your lack of shame amazes me.

86
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,628
( Polnareff chuckles )

87
00:03:48,662 --> 00:03:49,963
( Thinking )
For the love of--

88
00:03:49,997 --> 00:03:52,500
stop jabbing that stupid gun
into my head!

89
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:54,769
Wait! I may have found
a way out of this.

90
00:03:54,801 --> 00:03:58,171
I’ll give them a signal and
hope to god they figure it out.

91
00:03:58,205 --> 00:04:00,774
( Gulps )

92
00:04:00,807 --> 00:04:02,809
( Grunting )

93
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:07,514
- Avdol: Hmm?
- Jotaro: Huh?

94
00:04:07,548 --> 00:04:09,183
Joseph: Hmm.

95
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:11,185
( Polnareff grunting )

96
00:04:11,218 --> 00:04:13,220
♪

97
00:04:16,223 --> 00:04:17,691
Men: Hmm?

98
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:25,966
Hol horse: Hmm? Shit.

99
00:04:25,999 --> 00:04:27,434
Why’d they stop talking?

100
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:29,436
Polnareff: Well, as you can see,

101
00:04:29,469 --> 00:04:30,904
there’s nothing strange
going on here,

102
00:04:30,938 --> 00:04:32,640
so you can go on ahead.

103
00:04:32,673 --> 00:04:34,708
Avdol: Hmm? All right.

104
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:36,443
( Polnareff thinking )
i was lying.

105
00:04:36,476 --> 00:04:38,445
How are you not catching on?

106
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:40,447
My tongue. Look at my tongue.

107
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:43,550
He’s right behind me.
Please don’t leave.

108
00:04:43,584 --> 00:04:45,619
joseph:
Are you sure you’re okay?

109
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:46,953
You’re making a creepy face.

110
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:48,622
Something wrong
with your tongue?

111
00:04:48,655 --> 00:04:51,625
- ( Hol horse gasps )
- Avdol: No. That’s not it.

112
00:04:51,658 --> 00:04:53,627
he’s trying to tell us
that there’s something behind--

113
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:56,530
- ( Gasps )
- Polnareff: Shut your mouth.

114
00:04:56,563 --> 00:04:57,931
- Joseph: You mean...
- ( Mondatta scoffs )

115
00:04:57,965 --> 00:04:59,633
Hol horse: Damn it, polnareff,

116
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,535
you lowdown, dirty, son of a--

117
00:05:02,536 --> 00:05:04,505
you were cluing ’em in.

118
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:06,974
You’ve pissed me off
for the last time.

119
00:05:07,007 --> 00:05:10,611
I’ve had just about
enough of you. Now die.

120
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:12,513
- ( Polnareff sneezes )
- Hol horse: What the--

121
00:05:12,546 --> 00:05:14,114
( slow-motion sneeze )

122
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:17,884
( Slow-motion sneeze ) Huh?

123
00:05:17,918 --> 00:05:20,487
( Avdol gasps )
What’s he doing here?

124
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:24,759
hol horse: W-why?
You idiot, you had to sneeze?

125
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:25,792
( Both gasp )

126
00:05:28,295 --> 00:05:29,763
( Hol horse groans )

127
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:35,002
Polnareff: Everyone, watch out!
Hol horse is back,

128
00:05:35,035 --> 00:05:36,970
and he’s got a friend
hiding under the crate,

129
00:05:37,004 --> 00:05:37,972
so be careful!

130
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:39,573
Hol horse: Blast it!

131
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:41,541
This can’t be happening.

132
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:45,546
He sneezed, because I went and
jammed my fingers up his nose.

133
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:47,514
damn, damn.
If polnareff hadn’t sneezed,

134
00:05:47,548 --> 00:05:50,885
at the very least, I could have
gotten rid of him for good.

135
00:05:50,918 --> 00:05:53,621
I should have known better
than to team up

136
00:05:53,654 --> 00:05:57,191
with the likes of you, mondatta.
Now they’re gonna kill me.

137
00:05:57,224 --> 00:06:00,861
This is all happening because
of that blasted premonition.

138
00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:04,231
( Gasps )
Now i’m doomed!

139
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:07,901
man: Hey, bro,
you seeing what i’m seeing?

140
00:06:07,935 --> 00:06:10,070
It looks like that jackass
that picked a fight with us.

141
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:12,038
( Man #2 growls )

142
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:13,840
That’s him, all right.

143
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:16,643
I’ll never forget
the face of the bastard

144
00:06:16,677 --> 00:06:18,179
that blew my ear off!

145
00:06:18,212 --> 00:06:21,282
i’ll run him over
like a piece of roadkill!

146
00:06:22,316 --> 00:06:24,285
♪

147
00:06:28,655 --> 00:06:30,290
( Both gasp )

148
00:06:30,324 --> 00:06:31,826
Avdol: What?!

149
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:34,161
( All yell )

150
00:06:34,194 --> 00:06:36,063
Hol horse: Huh?

151
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:37,130
( Mondatta laughs )

152
00:06:37,164 --> 00:06:39,066
( Rubble clattering )

153
00:06:39,099 --> 00:06:41,702
Hol horse: S-seriously?

154
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:43,136
It all happened so fast,

155
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:45,305
they didn’t have a chance
to whip out their stands

156
00:06:45,339 --> 00:06:47,107
and stop the truck
from running ’em down.

157
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:51,211
My fingers went up his nose,
and the prediction came true.

158
00:06:51,245 --> 00:06:54,749
i can’t believe this!
I got all four of ’em at once!

159
00:06:54,781 --> 00:06:56,216
Mondatta: It’s fate.

160
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,853
My premonitions
are always right.

161
00:06:58,886 --> 00:07:02,223
However, it’s too soon
for you to finish them off.

162
00:07:02,256 --> 00:07:05,659
We must wait for the next
prediction to be revealed, yes.

163
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:07,294
Hol horse: Okay!

164
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:10,731
They proclaimed.

165
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:13,333
"The chance to finish off
their enemies had arrived.

166
00:07:13,367 --> 00:07:14,869
"But be careful, you two.

167
00:07:14,902 --> 00:07:18,105
Don’t rush in. Hide and wait."

168
00:07:18,138 --> 00:07:20,140
♪

169
00:07:20,174 --> 00:07:21,509
( Hol horse gulps )

170
00:07:21,542 --> 00:07:24,278
"’it’s still
too soon for us to move in.

171
00:07:24,311 --> 00:07:27,514
"’three of ’em are knocked out,
but jotaro’s still awake.

172
00:07:27,548 --> 00:07:31,118
He’s gonna get up
any second now.’"

173
00:07:31,151 --> 00:07:32,919
( gasps )

174
00:07:34,755 --> 00:07:37,858
- ( Glass tinkling )
- ( Jotaro groaning )

175
00:07:40,194 --> 00:07:41,529
( Hol horse growls )

176
00:07:41,562 --> 00:07:43,364
Jotaro wasn’t hit head-on
by the truck

177
00:07:43,397 --> 00:07:45,799
like Joseph and the others were.
That was close.

178
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,401
If we’d tried
creeping up to him,

179
00:07:47,434 --> 00:07:49,403
there’s a chance
he could have laid us out.

180
00:07:49,436 --> 00:07:51,772
Great. He’s lookin’ for me,

181
00:07:51,805 --> 00:07:53,507
probably wondering why I split

182
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:55,409
instead of blowin’
his head clear off

183
00:07:55,442 --> 00:07:57,711
when I thought
he was down for the count.

184
00:07:57,744 --> 00:08:01,147
we are gonna be able
to beat these yahoos, right?

185
00:08:01,181 --> 00:08:03,250
We’ve made it this far,
after all.

186
00:08:03,283 --> 00:08:05,152
i have to win,
no matter what it takes.

187
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:07,888
you got that?
Are you with me, mondatta?

188
00:08:07,921 --> 00:08:09,389
Mondatta: Yeah.

189
00:08:09,423 --> 00:08:12,192
Hol horse: We’re so close,
I can taste it!

190
00:08:12,226 --> 00:08:15,563
Mondatta, it’s time to take
these guys out once and for all,

191
00:08:15,596 --> 00:08:17,465
so what’s our next move?

192
00:08:17,498 --> 00:08:20,368
You’ve proven that your comic’s
predictions are 100% accurate.

193
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,169
i was wrong,
but I believe in you now,

194
00:08:23,203 --> 00:08:24,538
and i’ll do whatever I must.

195
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:26,706
Need me to stick my fingers
up something, I will.

196
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:29,409
Need me to eat crap, i’ll do it
without a second thought.

197
00:08:29,443 --> 00:08:33,180
I have to win this fight,
no matter what.

198
00:08:33,213 --> 00:08:34,214
Mondatta: Oh!

199
00:08:34,248 --> 00:08:35,616
Th-th-th-th-th-there it is!

200
00:08:35,649 --> 00:08:36,683
It’s here!

201
00:08:36,717 --> 00:08:39,353
I-it finally appeared, yes!

202
00:08:39,386 --> 00:08:42,322
- It’s the final prediction!
- Hol horse: What?

203
00:08:42,356 --> 00:08:43,958
Mondatta: "The time has arrived.

204
00:08:43,991 --> 00:08:46,760
"Hol horse’s next attack
will be his last.

205
00:08:46,793 --> 00:08:49,496
"While waiting to strike,
hol horse came across

206
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:51,332
"two plumbers
repairing drainpipes.

207
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:53,434
"he saw
the perfect opportunity to win

208
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:55,536
"and paid them
to open one of the pipes.

209
00:08:55,569 --> 00:08:58,605
"If hol horse were to fire
every last one of his bullets

210
00:08:58,639 --> 00:09:01,442
into that pipe exactly as
the clock struck 12:00 noon..."

211
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:02,776
- ( Pipe rattles )
- ( Hol horse gasps )

212
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:04,778
Plumber: Hey, check that out.

213
00:09:04,811 --> 00:09:07,480
Looks like there was a car
accident around the corner.

214
00:09:07,514 --> 00:09:09,316
plumber #2:
Who cares about that?

215
00:09:09,349 --> 00:09:10,884
let’s hurry
and finish this thing.

216
00:09:10,918 --> 00:09:12,820
Here. Hold this pipe for me.

217
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:14,321
Plumber #1: Okay.

218
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:19,026
♪

219
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:37,878
( Hol horse gasps )
W-what’s exactly gonna happen

220
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:40,247
if I fire my gun
into that pipe, huh?

221
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,648
( Mondatta groans )

222
00:09:41,682 --> 00:09:44,718
( Hol horse groaning )

223
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:46,653
come on!
Turn the damn page, would you?!

224
00:09:46,687 --> 00:09:48,722
I know I fire my gun
into the pipe,

225
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,724
but what happens after that?

226
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,425
Mondatta: "Once they’re fired,

227
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:54,861
"the bullets go through the pipe
and out the other end.

228
00:09:54,895 --> 00:09:57,998
Ka-boom! Hol horse’s bullets
hit their Mark

229
00:09:58,031 --> 00:09:59,933
and fly straight
through jotaro’s skull,

230
00:09:59,967 --> 00:10:02,536
right smack
in the middle of his forehead!"

231
00:10:02,569 --> 00:10:04,371
Yes. Yes! ( Laughs )

232
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:06,506
It’s finally happening! Yes!

233
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:07,975
Our time’s come, yes!

234
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:09,776
I’ve been waiting for this

235
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:12,680
since my brother’s accident,
yes! ( Laughing )

236
00:10:12,713 --> 00:10:14,481
hol horse:
That’s great, mondatta.

237
00:10:14,515 --> 00:10:17,718
I mean, it looks great,
but hold on a sec.

238
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:18,919
Mondatta: Hmm?

239
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:20,720
hol horse:
Let’s make sure we give it

240
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:23,857
a thorough once-over so we
don’t get our bacon cooked. Huh?

241
00:10:23,891 --> 00:10:26,427
W-what’s happening
on this page?

242
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,629
Hey, this is the prediction

243
00:10:28,662 --> 00:10:31,031
from when your brother
tried to wipe out jotaro.

244
00:10:31,064 --> 00:10:32,599
But in the end,

245
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:34,969
your brother was the one
who got himself blown up.

246
00:10:35,002 --> 00:10:38,339
Mondatta: Yeah, but my brother
transformed himself into jotaro

247
00:10:38,372 --> 00:10:39,874
without giving it any thought.

248
00:10:39,907 --> 00:10:42,877
If he hadn’t, the prediction
would have come true, yes.

249
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,479
b-b-but that’s
not going to happen to us,

250
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:48,815
because you and I can’t
transform ourselves, yes.

251
00:10:48,849 --> 00:10:50,517
Hol horse: Oh, yeah,
you’re right.

252
00:10:50,551 --> 00:10:51,986
I don’t have changing powers,

253
00:10:52,019 --> 00:10:55,389
so I couldn’t pretend
to be jotaro if I wanted to.

254
00:10:55,422 --> 00:10:57,791
Wait! Then does that mean...

255
00:10:57,825 --> 00:10:59,927
Mondatta: It does indeed, yes!

256
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:02,996
At last I can avenge
my brother, yes!

257
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:06,700
There’s absolutely no way to
misinterpret this prophecy, yes.

258
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:09,903
All you have to do is shoot
your bullets into this pipe,

259
00:11:09,937 --> 00:11:13,107
and jotaro
will meet his maker, yes!

260
00:11:14,107 --> 00:11:15,842
( Sighs )

261
00:11:15,876 --> 00:11:17,010
( Hol horse laughs )

262
00:11:18,378 --> 00:11:20,013
( Gasps )
Let’s back up a bit.

263
00:11:20,047 --> 00:11:22,449
It gave us a specific time
to do it, right?

264
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:24,884
It’s gotta be done
by the stroke of noon.

265
00:11:24,918 --> 00:11:28,088
Hmm.

266
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:29,856
Huh?! Hey!

267
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:32,126
Your magic prediction comic book
neglected to mention

268
00:11:32,159 --> 00:11:34,895
we only have two minutes left
before 12:00.

269
00:11:34,928 --> 00:11:36,029
( Grumbles )

270
00:11:36,063 --> 00:11:37,865
Mondatta: D-don’t panic!

271
00:11:37,898 --> 00:11:41,502
All you have to do is
aim your gun and fire, yes.

272
00:11:41,535 --> 00:11:43,637
you have more
than enough time, yes.

273
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:46,006
Just believe in fate.
It’ll work itself out.

274
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,541
Hol horse: Yeah, I know. I know!

275
00:11:47,574 --> 00:11:48,809
It’s 100%

276
00:11:48,842 --> 00:11:51,545
I believe you.
I really do, but...

277
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:53,580
( Watch ticking )

278
00:11:53,614 --> 00:11:56,584
We’re down to the wire,
and time’s against us.

279
00:11:56,617 --> 00:11:59,420
I’ve gotta haul ass!

280
00:11:59,453 --> 00:12:01,121
You there, worker guys,
listen up!

281
00:12:01,154 --> 00:12:03,523
This is a matter
of life and death.

282
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:05,926
I need one of you to open
that pipe on the double!

283
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:08,929
- Plumber #2: Hmm?
- Plumber #1: Huh?

284
00:12:08,962 --> 00:12:10,564
hol horse:
Just do it, all right?

285
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:12,532
Plumber #1: Hey, who exactly

286
00:12:12,566 --> 00:12:14,401
do you think
you’re barking orders at?

287
00:12:14,434 --> 00:12:16,636
Plumber #2: Who do think
you are, pal? Take a hike.

288
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:19,506
Hol horse: Open the pipe,
or you can die!

289
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:21,842
Mondatta: Hol horse, you should
know that ordinary people

290
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:24,411
don’t have the ability
to see your stand, yes.

291
00:12:24,444 --> 00:12:25,412
Hol horse: Huh?

292
00:12:25,445 --> 00:12:27,414
Plumbers: Huh?

293
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:29,549
Mondatta: According to
the premonition in the comic,

294
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:31,852
you’re supposed to pay
the workers, yes.

295
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:33,019
Hol horse: Huh? Pay them?

296
00:12:34,188 --> 00:12:35,723
( Squeals )

297
00:12:35,756 --> 00:12:37,958
Only a minute, ten seconds left
before showtime!

298
00:12:37,991 --> 00:12:40,694
All right, all right,
sorry about the attitude.

299
00:12:40,727 --> 00:12:41,995
I’ll pay you to open the pipe,

300
00:12:42,029 --> 00:12:44,198
but you have to do it now!
Please.

301
00:12:44,231 --> 00:12:46,600
Plumber #2: Now you’re
gonna pay us? Weirdo.

302
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:49,202
Why would you give us money
to open the pipe?

303
00:12:49,236 --> 00:12:50,804
plumber #1:
Does it really matter?

304
00:12:50,838 --> 00:12:52,073
Hand over what you got.

305
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,573
Hol horse: Yeah, okay.

306
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:57,211
( Gasps )

307
00:12:57,244 --> 00:12:58,679
Oh, no. Where is--

308
00:12:58,712 --> 00:13:00,013
plumber #1:
Yo, what’s the holdup, man?

309
00:13:00,047 --> 00:13:02,516
( Hol horse yelps )
I’m flat broke!

310
00:13:02,549 --> 00:13:05,218
oh, that’s right.
I left my wallet at the hotel!

311
00:13:05,252 --> 00:13:06,587
Plumber #1: Huh?

312
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:07,855
plumber #2:
What’s with this guy?

313
00:13:07,888 --> 00:13:09,656
Hol horse: Mondatta!

314
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:11,025
Remember the money
I gave to you

315
00:13:11,058 --> 00:13:12,726
just in case
you ended up getting lost?

316
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:14,794
Well, I need you
to give it back to me,

317
00:13:14,828 --> 00:13:16,496
so fork it over now, mondatta!

318
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:17,898
Mondatta: Right. Let’s see.

319
00:13:17,931 --> 00:13:20,767
hol horse: Crap!
We’ve only got 40 seconds left.

320
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:22,870
Move your ass!

321
00:13:22,903 --> 00:13:25,506
Mondatta: I-I don’t know
if this is enough,

322
00:13:25,539 --> 00:13:28,709
but go ahead, and take it.
( Yelps )

323
00:13:28,742 --> 00:13:30,611
( Hol horse shrieks )

324
00:13:30,644 --> 00:13:33,480
plumber #2: Hey,
I think I saw one of ’em

325
00:13:33,514 --> 00:13:35,149
roll behind the bricks.

326
00:13:35,182 --> 00:13:38,819
They’re just coins, but there
are a lot of ’em. Nice.

327
00:13:38,852 --> 00:13:40,620
plumber #1:
Must be at least £20.

328
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:42,656
Hey, man, watch your feet.
You’re steppin’ on one.

329
00:13:42,689 --> 00:13:44,491
- Plumber #2: What’s that?
- ( Hol horse screams )

330
00:13:44,525 --> 00:13:46,927
Pick the damn coins up later!
You can have ’em all, okay?

331
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:49,029
Woman: Here you go, boys.

332
00:13:49,062 --> 00:13:51,064
It’s getting close to noon.

333
00:13:51,098 --> 00:13:52,666
I made you boys some tea,

334
00:13:52,699 --> 00:13:55,068
so take a load off,
and have some lunch.

335
00:13:55,102 --> 00:13:56,870
plumber #2:
Oh, sounds good to me.

336
00:13:56,904 --> 00:13:59,673
Hol horse: Listen, granny!
I found ’em first, so get lost!

337
00:13:59,706 --> 00:14:01,641
plumber #1:
Thank you very much, ma’am.

338
00:14:03,277 --> 00:14:04,712
Hol horse: Put ’em down!

339
00:14:04,745 --> 00:14:06,947
I told you to hurry up
and open the pipe!

340
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:08,682
if you don’t,
i’ll crack your skulls!

341
00:14:08,715 --> 00:14:10,283
( Plumbers whimper )

342
00:14:15,622 --> 00:14:17,290
Plumber #1: There. It’s open.

343
00:14:17,324 --> 00:14:18,559
Hol horse: Move it!

344
00:14:18,592 --> 00:14:20,828
( Yells )

345
00:14:20,861 --> 00:14:23,630
Now die, jotaro!

346
00:14:24,898 --> 00:14:26,266
♪

347
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,602
i won!
Just like the prediction said,

348
00:14:28,635 --> 00:14:31,271
I shot the cocky bastard
at the stroke of noon.

349
00:14:31,305 --> 00:14:33,207
Go get him.

350
00:14:40,914 --> 00:14:42,883
Jotaro: Old man, time to get up.

351
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,084
( Both grunt )

352
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:49,155
Joseph: Uh, I don’t think
there’s any permanent damage.

353
00:14:49,189 --> 00:14:52,659
( Avdol groans )
I only have cuts and bruises.

354
00:14:52,693 --> 00:14:54,662
But polnareff,
on the other hand...

355
00:14:54,695 --> 00:14:55,996
Joseph: Hmm?

356
00:14:56,029 --> 00:14:58,565
polnareff: Hey,
don’t mean to be a nuisance,

357
00:14:58,599 --> 00:15:01,368
but could someone
get this damn thing off of me?

358
00:15:03,937 --> 00:15:05,906
( Grunting )

359
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:07,607
Hol horse: I won.

360
00:15:07,641 --> 00:15:08,876
This is really gonna happen.

361
00:15:08,909 --> 00:15:11,011
jotaro is
right in front of that pipe.

362
00:15:11,044 --> 00:15:12,812
♪

363
00:15:20,687 --> 00:15:22,088
( Polnareff sniffles )

364
00:15:22,122 --> 00:15:24,625
- ( Sneezes )
- Jotaro: Ugh!

365
00:15:28,729 --> 00:15:30,297
Both: What?!

366
00:15:32,199 --> 00:15:33,734
Jotaro: Watch it.

367
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:36,103
( Polnareff sputters )
Sorry about that, jotaro.

368
00:15:36,136 --> 00:15:38,338
i don’t know
what hol horse was thinking,

369
00:15:38,372 --> 00:15:40,374
but he decided
sticking his fingers up my nose

370
00:15:40,407 --> 00:15:42,342
would be the perfect way
to spend the evening.

371
00:15:42,376 --> 00:15:45,179
That guy is tres disgusting.

372
00:15:45,212 --> 00:15:48,882
Man, my nose still itches.
So sorry again.

373
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:51,152
hol horse:
But how’s it possible?

374
00:15:51,185 --> 00:15:53,154
My bullets missed!

375
00:15:53,187 --> 00:15:54,355
( Mondatta gasping )

376
00:15:54,388 --> 00:15:56,724
Hol horse: What the hell?!

377
00:15:56,757 --> 00:15:59,126
were you trying
to pull one over on me?

378
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:01,628
What the hell is
going on around here?!

379
00:16:01,662 --> 00:16:03,297
Mondatta: I have no idea, yes!

380
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:07,067
Like I said, m-my predictions
always come true! It’s fate!

381
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,234
I can’t believe it.

382
00:16:08,268 --> 00:16:10,804
Not once since I
started using my stand

383
00:16:10,838 --> 00:16:12,673
have my predictions
ever been wrong!

384
00:16:12,706 --> 00:16:15,209
Hol horse: Well, clearly there’s
a first time for everything,

385
00:16:15,242 --> 00:16:16,310
’cause they’re still alive.

386
00:16:16,343 --> 00:16:18,178
Not a single bullet
hit its Mark.

387
00:16:18,212 --> 00:16:20,881
It’s safe to say your prediction
was totally wrong.

388
00:16:20,914 --> 00:16:22,382
( Growls ) Damn you!

389
00:16:22,416 --> 00:16:25,986
Announcer: Thanks for joining us
for today’s broadcast.

390
00:16:26,019 --> 00:16:29,689
Be sure to tune in next time.
Now for the 12:00 news.

391
00:16:31,091 --> 00:16:32,192
Both: Huh?

392
00:16:32,226 --> 00:16:33,227
( Hol horse yells )

393
00:16:35,062 --> 00:16:36,397
What the hell?

394
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:39,400
There’s no way in hell
it’s just now noon.

395
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:40,801
( Gasps )

396
00:16:40,834 --> 00:16:42,269
I know what happened.

397
00:16:42,302 --> 00:16:44,704
M-my watch is...

398
00:16:46,039 --> 00:16:48,408
My watch is fast!

399
00:16:48,442 --> 00:16:51,412
And that means I ended up
firing off the bullets

400
00:16:51,445 --> 00:16:54,181
before it was time,
but now it is noon.

401
00:16:54,214 --> 00:16:56,383
- ( Bell chiming )
- What’s that mean for us, huh?

402
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:58,952
Tell me. What the hell’s
gonna happen to us

403
00:16:58,986 --> 00:17:01,755
now that we’ve
gone off script?

404
00:17:01,788 --> 00:17:04,124
Mondatta: No, it can’t be.

405
00:17:07,995 --> 00:17:09,396
( Gasps )

406
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:11,264
Hol horse: But where
did we get off track?

407
00:17:11,298 --> 00:17:13,934
It said the bullets would go
right through jotaro’s forehead

408
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:15,168
at the stroke of noon.

409
00:17:15,202 --> 00:17:16,804
Mondatta: Hol horse,
the bullets are--

410
00:17:16,837 --> 00:17:18,172
hol horse: Come on.

411
00:17:18,205 --> 00:17:20,174
all I need to know
is what’s gonna happen next.

412
00:17:20,207 --> 00:17:22,309
( Bullets whizzing )

413
00:17:22,342 --> 00:17:24,044
( Gasps )

414
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:25,111
( Mondatta gasps )

415
00:17:25,145 --> 00:17:27,848
( Hol horse screams )

416
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:29,850
( Glass shatters )

417
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:31,184
Jotaro: Hmm?

418
00:17:31,218 --> 00:17:33,887
Polnareff: Hey, tell me
i’m not the only one

419
00:17:33,921 --> 00:17:35,289
who heard
that ear-piercing scream.

420
00:17:35,322 --> 00:17:37,424
Joseph: I’m not clear
on the details,

421
00:17:37,457 --> 00:17:39,326
but there’s something fishy
going on here.

422
00:17:39,359 --> 00:17:41,261
But the bigger concern
is this truck.

423
00:17:41,295 --> 00:17:43,297
i think we’d
better get out of here

424
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:44,865
before the cops
start showing up.

425
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:45,866
Let’s move, men.

426
00:17:45,899 --> 00:17:47,367
Polnareff: But before we go,

427
00:17:47,401 --> 00:17:50,104
i wanna know
where hol horse ran off to.

428
00:17:50,137 --> 00:17:53,107
jotaro: I don’t know.
He disappeared for some reason.

429
00:17:54,308 --> 00:17:55,276
( Grunts )

430
00:17:55,309 --> 00:17:57,344
( Groans )

431
00:17:59,079 --> 00:18:01,315
Avdol: Hey, if you don’t
get away from that pipe,

432
00:18:01,348 --> 00:18:02,983
you’re going to get soaking wet.

433
00:18:03,016 --> 00:18:05,151
You should try
to be more careful.

434
00:18:05,185 --> 00:18:06,153
Jotaro: Hmph.

435
00:18:06,186 --> 00:18:08,155
( Siren blaring )

436
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:12,926
Officer: Is he dead?

437
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,962
officer #2:
No, but he’s critical.

438
00:18:14,995 --> 00:18:18,499
I couldn’t even begin to tell
you what transpired here today.

439
00:18:18,532 --> 00:18:21,902
They looked him over, and it
seems as though the bullet

440
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:24,538
went through his forehead
and out the top of his head.

441
00:18:24,571 --> 00:18:27,307
one centimeter lower,
and he would have been a goner.

442
00:18:27,341 --> 00:18:30,411
Whew. Gotta say
that is one lucky man.

443
00:18:30,444 --> 00:18:32,446
( Siren blaring )

444
00:18:35,048 --> 00:18:38,885
Mondatta: In the end, it seems
my prediction was right,

445
00:18:38,919 --> 00:18:42,823
which means this was
hol horse’s fate all along.

446
00:18:42,856 --> 00:18:45,425
Jotaro is really something else.

447
00:18:45,459 --> 00:18:48,128
How lucky can one person be?

448
00:18:48,162 --> 00:18:51,399
Both my brother and hol horse
were defeated by fate.

449
00:18:51,431 --> 00:18:54,467
At this point, we stand users
are wasting our time.

450
00:18:54,501 --> 00:18:57,437
Master dio’s the only one
who can defeat him.

451
00:18:59,406 --> 00:19:01,041
You know what, zenyatta?

452
00:19:01,074 --> 00:19:03,910
hol horse,
that big buffoon of a man,

453
00:19:03,944 --> 00:19:05,179
taught me that revenge

454
00:19:05,212 --> 00:19:07,481
is nothing more
than a massive joke,

455
00:19:07,514 --> 00:19:11,051
so i’m going
to forget about jotaro.

456
00:19:11,084 --> 00:19:13,253
I have a new path in life.

457
00:19:13,287 --> 00:19:17,391
I’ll use my stand’s powers
to help as many people as I can.

458
00:19:17,424 --> 00:19:20,060
I’ll use them to bring
happiness to everyone.

459
00:19:20,093 --> 00:19:22,395
maybe people
will start to like us,

460
00:19:22,429 --> 00:19:25,132
and just maybe
our future will be brighter.

461
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:28,602
♪

462
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,906
I’m tired of being afraid.
Today’s the last day

463
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:35,409
I spend under a box
cowering from everyone.

464
00:19:35,442 --> 00:19:37,844
I learned a lot
from this battle,

465
00:19:37,878 --> 00:19:39,546
more than I thought I could.

466
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:41,282
I’m coming home now, brother.

467
00:19:41,315 --> 00:19:44,018
I’m coming home to aswan
to join you.

468
00:19:45,452 --> 00:19:47,354
- ( Iggy yelps )
- ( Mondatta gasps ) Eh?

469
00:19:47,387 --> 00:19:49,856
Oh, my gosh, I am so sorry!

470
00:19:49,890 --> 00:19:51,925
I kicked it without thinking.

471
00:19:51,959 --> 00:19:55,062
I didn’t mean to hit you.
Please forgive me.

472
00:19:55,095 --> 00:19:57,264
Hold on. This dog...

473
00:19:57,297 --> 00:19:58,865
He looks familiar.

474
00:19:58,899 --> 00:20:02,035
I pretty sure i’ve seen him
before, but where?

475
00:20:02,069 --> 00:20:03,637
( Iggy growling )

476
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:05,972
( Mondatta yells )
There’s no way!

477
00:20:06,006 --> 00:20:08,041
- It can’t be!
- ( Iggy growling )

478
00:20:08,075 --> 00:20:13,047
Mondatta: No!

479
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:15,416
polnareff: Hey,
now that I think about it,

480
00:20:15,449 --> 00:20:17,051
where’d our dumb-ass dog go?

481
00:20:17,084 --> 00:20:18,919
Joseph: You talking about iggy?

482
00:20:18,952 --> 00:20:21,288
I’m sure he’s scrounging around
for food somewhere.

483
00:20:21,321 --> 00:20:22,989
Avdol: I’ve said
from the beginning

484
00:20:23,023 --> 00:20:24,658
he wouldn’t help us
when we needed him.

485
00:20:26,493 --> 00:20:29,062
Mondatta: "He should have known
it wouldn’t be so simple.

486
00:20:29,096 --> 00:20:31,131
"If people could change
that easily,

487
00:20:31,165 --> 00:20:32,700
life wouldn’t be so hard."

488
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:35,202
"So as fate would have it,

489
00:20:35,235 --> 00:20:37,571
"mondatta joined hol horse
in the hospital,

490
